  "prompt": "What are some side dishes for tortellini?",
  "response": "Tortellini is a versatile dish that pairs well with a variety of side dishes, depending on the sauce and flavor profile you're going for. Here are some ideas, categorized for easier choosing:\n\n**For a Simple, Fresh, and Light Meal:**\n\n*   **Simple Green Salad:** A classic choice! A mix of greens with a light vinaigrette dressing (Italian, lemon, or balsamic) is refreshing. Add some cherry tomatoes, cucumbers, or shaved Parmesan for extra flavor.\n*   **Asparagus:** Roasted, steamed, or grilled asparagus is a delicious and elegant choice. A squeeze of lemon and a sprinkle of Parmesan are all it needs.\n*   **Steamed or Saut\u00e9ed Spinach:**  Simple, nutritious, and cooks quickly. Add a little garlic and olive oil for flavor.\n*   **Caprese Salad:** Fresh mozzarella, tomatoes, and basil, drizzled with balsamic glaze. It's bright, flavorful, and visually appealing.\n*   **Arugula Salad with Lemon Vinaigrette:** Arugula's peppery bite complements the richness of the tortellini.  Add some shaved Parmesan or toasted pine nuts for added texture and flavor.\n\n**For a Heartier Meal:**\n\n*   **Roasted Vegetables:**  A medley of roasted vegetables like bell peppers, zucchini, onions, eggplant, and carrots is a satisfying and flavorful option.\n*   **Garlic Bread or Bruschetta:** Perfect for soaking up any extra sauce!\n*   **Italian Sausage:** Grilled or pan-fried Italian sausage adds a savory and meaty element to the meal.\n*   **Creamed Spinach:** A richer and more decadent take on spinach, perfect for a special occasion.\n*   **Saut\u00e9ed Mushrooms:** Mushrooms, especially when saut\u00e9ed with garlic and herbs, provide an earthy and umami-rich flavor that pairs well with many tortellini fillings.\n\n**For a Mediterranean Vibe:**\n\n*   **Greek Salad:**  Cucumbers, tomatoes, red onion, olives, feta cheese, and a simple vinaigrette.\n*   **Roasted Red Peppers:**  Sweet and smoky roasted red peppers can be served on their own or used as a topping for crostini.\n*   **Artichoke Hearts:** Marinated or grilled artichoke hearts offer a unique and slightly tangy flavor.\n\n**Considerations when Choosing a Side:**\n\n*   **Tortellini Sauce:**  The sauce on your tortellini will greatly influence your side dish choice.  Creamy sauces pair well with lighter, fresher sides, while tomato-based sauces can handle heartier, roasted vegetables.\n*   **Tortellini Filling:** The filling of your tortellini also matters. Cheese tortellini is very versatile, while meat-filled tortellini may pair better with lighter sides to balance the richness.\n*   **Seasonality:**  Choose seasonal vegetables for the freshest and most flavorful side dishes.\n*   **Dietary Restrictions:**  Be mindful of any dietary restrictions your guests may have.\n\nNo matter what you choose, make sure the flavors complement each other and create a well-rounded and delicious meal!  Enjoy!\n",
